##1 Selecting Predictor

After evaluation of many variables that has positive or negative relationship between unemploymeny , I have chosen five potential predictors that are capacity utilization rate of manufacturing , dollar exchange rate , firms statistics(newly established),interest rate,firms statistics(newly closed).

That is plot of unemployment for 85 weeks below.

##2 Building Linear Model

Especially, we have nice correlationships for some indepedent variables,which pushes me to build linear model to check if our model is good enough or not.

Summary of inear regression model we build above helps us claim that we have good model because of p value of model that is 3.415e-14.

However, we are not able to be sure that every independent variable is supposed to be in our model.Particularly,interest rate has greater t value and that is triggering me to question if its presence in that model is beneficial or not.However,before that I tend to visualize predictions of this model for better approach.

Variance seems a bit deviated.On the other hand,I can see positive linear relationship which indicates that I am on right way.

Then,we benefit from step function in R to question presences of independent variables in my model.

##3 Evaluation of Search Keyword

My prediction about search keyword that can be relevant to the measures I considered above is Unemployment Salary.That is so expected that unemployed people are likely to search for unemployment salary in need of money.Then, observing visualization of data taken from Google Trends Data for search volume of unemployment salary (click for access) enables us to see whether any correlation between that and other histograms.
